	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Right, and you will have to run the music init code (FamiToneInit) and the sfx init code (FamiToneSfxInit) (to set pointers to the start of the music / sfx) at the start of your program , then play a song / sfx with the FamiToneMusicPlay and FamiToneSfxPlay subroutines.<br /><br />One per frame call FamiToneUpdate, to update the music (run the music engine).<br /><br />I think this explains it...<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://timcheeseman.com/nesdev/2018/02/03/a-lifetime-of-happines-part-two.html">https://timcheeseman.com/nesdev/2018/02 ... t-two.html</a><!-- m -->

		

